<p>Chris, since guns were already invented by the time Libertopia was founded and the inventor didn&#8217;t live in Libertopia, they held an auction. (This is by analogy to the spectrum auctions some libertarians have advocated.)</p>

<p>I don&#8217;t think taking the guns is too hard to believe, since the government routinely takes unauthorized copyrighted material and gives it to the copyright holder. (Example: <a href="http://foetusized.org/u2.html">Negativland&#8217;s U2</a>.) I don&#8217;t know for surehow copyright-is-property libertarians feel about this practice, though, but I assume they support it. </p>

<p>Gil is insane and has no friends.</p>

<p>Presumably Seth&#8217;s version of Libertopia is a joke, because it sounds like a gun control police state.</p>

