</div><div id="c351">

<p>One of the concepts behind libertarianism is that they want the gov&#8217;t to be small above all else.  IP/spectrum laws are just too damn easy to break (see P2P, any UI code that breaks Apple&#8217;s patents, any moron with a soldering iron and some radio components), and they victimless (nothing is taken away from anyone else (see Jefferson&#8217;s idea == candle meme)).  Only a large, intrusive gov&#8217;t could hope to enforce IP/spectrum law.  </p>

<p>Property is important in Libertopia, but not so important that giving up the other principle of Freedom.</p>

